title: For Sale/Trade:  AK/Saiga 7.62
postcontent: This is the closest thing you can own to a Russian made AK-47. They are made in the same factory, but Saigas have a certain number of parts in their unmodified “Sporting” configuration. They are considered imported because they have more than 10 imported parts in them. As such they are held to 922(r) compliance.You can convert it to a pistol grip (unsporting) configuration, but you have to take out some Russian parts and replace them with American made parts. If you want to use high capacity magazines, convert the weapon to pistol grip configuration or use a flash hider, it will then be considered unsporting. You will need to swap out parts so that you have no more than 10 imported parts in it. It will then be considered a US made firearm and 922(r) does not apply.This is an unmolested, untouched, unconverted Saiga with all Russian parts that is ready to be converted. Manufactured by Izhmash (now Kalashnikov). Less than 100 rounds since new. I always planned to convert it, but never got around to it. I'm looking to get in to something new. Includes several boxes of ammo and 1 magazine. Open to trades or reasonable offers.
